# Project Rules

## Project Overview
This is a ready-to-use setup for AI-powered code editing using VS Code + Cline + OpenRouter.

## Code Style
- Use clear, readable code
- Add comments for complex logic
- Follow language-specific conventions
- Keep functions small and focused

## Testing
- Write tests for new features
- Test edge cases and error conditions
- Keep tests up to date with code changes
- Use descriptive test names

## Documentation
- Update README for major changes
- Document API endpoints and functions
- Keep code comments current and helpful
- Write clear commit messages

## File Organization
- Keep related files together
- Use meaningful file and folder names
- Separate configuration from code
- Maintain clean project structure

## AI Assistant Guidelines
- Always explain what code does
- Suggest improvements when appropriate
- Ask clarifying questions when requirements are unclear
- Provide working, tested code examples

## Memory Bank Usage
- Use /memory-bank to update project context
- Keep activeContext.md current with recent changes
- Update progress.md after major milestones
- Document important decisions in systemPatterns.md
